race.comment: BOGUES (5) ran a good race fresh at Kyneton over 1865m, battling away to finish a neck behind DURBAN HARBOUR (2) who got through the wet conditions best to score at a big price. Fancy BOGUES can turn the tables on DURBAN HARBOUR with that run under the belt from a good draw. SUNTORA (7) was outclassed in a rich race at Flemington last time behind some good mares. The run two back at Pakenham over 1400m was good and Zahra aboard is a good push. OCEANS ABOVE (6) ran well here last time out over this route when getting back from a wide gate and running on for fourth. Gets the switch to barrier one here and Williams on is a significant jockey change. TOO BIG (4) continues to race very well and can give a sight.
